BoundAttributes.Documentation:

BoundAttributes.Name: Crossfade
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Animate slides with a fade transition instead of a slide.

BoundAttributes.Name: Interval
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

<summary>
            Specifies whether to show an indicator for each slide.

BoundAttributes.Name: ShowControls

<summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SelectedSlide

<summary>
            Gets or sets currently selected slide name.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SelectedSlideChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Occurs after the selected slide has changed.
            </summary>

<summary>
            The pattern attribute specifies a regular expression that the input element's value is checked against on form validation.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ChangeTextOnKeyPress
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If true the text in will be changed after each key press.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            Note that setting this will override global settings in <see cref="P:Blazorise.BlazoriseOptions.ChangeTextOnKeyPress" />.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: DelayTextOnKeyPress
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If true the entered text will be slightly delayed before submitting it to the internal value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: DelayTextOnKeyPressInterval
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Interval in milliseconds that entered text will be delayed from submitting to the internal value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Size

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ReadOnly
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Add the readonly boolean attribute on an input to prevent modification of the input’s value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Disabled
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Add the disabled boolean attribute on an input to prevent user interactions and make it appear lighter.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CustomValidationValue

<summary>

            the <see cref="P:Blazorise.Validation.Validator" /> handler.

            Should be used carefully as it's only meant for some special cases when input is used

            </remarks>

TagHelpers.Name: Blazorise.InputMask
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            Format input text content when you are typing.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Value
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the input time value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ValueChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Occurs when the time has changed.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ValueExpression
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets an expression that identifies the time field.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Mask
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The mask to use for the input.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Regex
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Use a regular expression as a mask.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Alias
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            With an alias, you can define a complex mask definition and call it by using an alias name.
            So this is mainly to simplify the use of your masks. Some aliases found in the extensions are email,
            currency, decimal, integer, date, DateTime, dd/mm/yyyy, etc.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: InputFormat
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines the input format when the <see cref="P:Blazorise.InputMask.Alias" /> is used.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OutputFormat
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines the output format of the <see cref="P:Blazorise.InputMask.Value" /> when the <see cref="P:Blazorise.InputMask.Alias" /> is used.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ShowMaskOnFocus
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Shows the mask when the input gets focus. (default = true)
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ShowMaskOnHover
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Shows the mask when hovering the mouse. (default = true)
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: NumericInput
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Numeric input direction. Keeps the caret at the end.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: RightAlign
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Align the input to the right.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            By setting the rightAlign you can specify to right-align an inputmask. This is only applied
            in combination op the numericInput option or the dir-attribute. The default is true.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: DecimalSeparator
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Define the decimal separator (numeric mode only).
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: GroupSeparator
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Define the group separator (numeric mode only).
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Nullable
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Return nothing when the user hasn't entered anything. Default: false.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AutoUnmask
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Automatically unmask the value when retrieved. Default: false.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: PositionCaretOnClick
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines the positioning of the caret on click.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ClearMaskOnLostFocus
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Remove the empty mask on blur or when not empty remove the optional trailing part. Default: true
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ClearIncomplete
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Clear the incomplete input on blur. Default: false
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Completed
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Execute a function when the mask is completed.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Incompleted
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Execute a function when the mask is incomplete. Executes on blur.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Cleared
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Execute a function when the mask is cleared.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Placeholder
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Sets the placeholder for the empty text.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Plaintext
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Sets the class to remove the default form field styling and preserve the correct margin and padding.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Color
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Sets the input text color.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Pattern
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The pattern attribute specifies a regular expression that the input element's value is checked against on form validation.

            If set to true, and <see cref="P:Blazorise.Validations.Mode" /> is set to <see cref="F:Blazorise.ValidationMode.Auto" />, validation will run automatically on page load.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            When validation is placed inside of modal dialog, the behavior is a little different. 
            Modals are by definition always loaded and are always present in the DOM so no loading is ever happening again
            after the page that contains the modal is first initialized.  Their visibility is controlled by display: none;
            To workaround this, the actual "first load" for modals can be done by re-initializing <see cref="P:Blazorise.Validations.Model" /> parameter. 
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: EditContext
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Supplies the edit context explicitly. If using this parameter, do not
            also supply <see cref="P:Blazorise.Validations.Model" />, since the model value will be taken
            from the <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Forms.EditContext.Model" /> property.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Model
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the top-level model object for the form. An edit context will be constructed for this model.
            If using this parameter, do not also supply a value for <see cref="P:Blazorise.Validations.EditContext" />.
            </summary>

TagHelpers.Name: Attributes
TagHelpers.Documentation: Merges a collection of attributes into the current element or component.

BoundAttributes.Name: @attributes
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Merges a collection of attributes into the current element or component.

TagHelpers.Name: Bind
TagHelpers.Documentation: Binds the provided expression to an attribute and a change event, based on the naming of the bind attribute. For example: @bind-value="..." and @bind-value:event="onchange" will assign the current value of the expression to the 'value' attribute, and assign a delegate that attempts to set the value to the 'onchange' attribute.

BoundAttributes.Name: @bind-...
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Binds the provided expression to an attribute and a change event, based on the naming of the bind attribute. For example: @bind-value="..." and @bind-value:event="onchange" will assign the current value of the expression to the 'value' attribute, and assign a delegate that attempts to set the value to the 'onchange' attribute.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: format
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies a format to convert the value specified by the corresponding bind attribute. For example: @bind-value:format="..." will apply a format string to the value specified in @bind-value="...". The format string can currently only be used with expressions of type DateTime.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: event
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies the event handler name to attach for change notifications for the value provided by the '@bind-...' attribute.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: culture
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies the culture to use for conversions.
